import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import json

# scraper function
def scraper(url: str) -> str:
  # get html content from url
  html = requests.get(url).content
  # initialize BeautifulSoup object with html content
  soup = BeautifulSoup(html, 'html.parser')
  # find all question summaries
  question_summaries = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'question-summary'})
  # initialize list to store scraped data
  scraped_data = []
  # loop through question summaries
  for question_summary in question_summaries:
    # extract question title
    question_title = question_summary.find('a', {'class': 'question-hyperlink'}).text
    # extract tags
    tags = [tag.text for tag in question_summary.find('a', {'class': 'post-tag'})]
    # extract user name
    user_name = question_summary.find('div', {'class': 'user-details'}).find('a').text
    # create dictionary with scraped data
    data = {'question_title': question_title, 'tags': tags, 'user_name': user_name}
    # add dictionary to list
    scraped_data.append(data)
  
  # print scraped data as JSON
  print(json.dumps(scraped_data, indent=2))

if __name__ == '__main__':
  url = "https://math.stackexchange.com/questions"
  scraper(url) # call scraper function with given url
